    {
      "id": "research-context-assumptions",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Twilite Context and Assumptions",
      "position": {
        "x": 460,
        "y": 20
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 500,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Twilite Context and Working Assumptions\n\nWhat `twilite.zone` establishes:\n- Twilite is a persistent graph workspace where ideas connect and evolve\n- the canvas is graph-shaped and first-class\n- collaboration with an AI assistant is a core feature\n- the graph is treated as a durable and portable artifact shared between humans and agents\n- public indexing suggests deeper structures around ontology, node classes, and documentation\n\nConservative assumptions for design:\n- the graph has stable node and edge IDs\n- some notion of node and edge typing either exists or is wanted\n- the AI assistant consumes structure plus properties as context\n- least-regret designs should preserve persistence, replay, and collaboration even if storage/runtime changes later\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
