    {
      "id": "research-graph-models",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Graph Models and Fundamentals",
      "position": {
        "x": 1080,
        "y": 20
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 620,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Graph Models and Fundamentals to Operationalize\n\nRecommended stance for Twilite:\n- edge directedness should be semantic per edge type, not a single global graph choice\n- weights should exist when relationships need strength, cost, confidence, or recency signals\n- parallel edges should be allowed, either as a multigraph or as typed property-graph edges with unique IDs\n- time should be first-class enough to support version snapshots, deltas, provenance, and reproducibility\n- higher-arity relationships can be modeled either as hyperedges or, more practically for Twilite, as relationship nodes\n- a property graph is the most operational baseline because both nodes and edges need attributes\n\nOperational consequences:\n- persistence and merge logic need stable IDs and event history\n- query APIs need edge-type awareness and direction semantics\n- the AI layer needs explicit graph meaning, not just a canvas screenshot\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
