    {
      "id": "research-algorithms",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Algorithms and Complexity",
      "position": {
        "x": 1760,
        "y": 20
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 700,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Algorithms and Complexity in a Twilite Context\n\nAlgorithm families worth productizing:\n- traversal for neighborhood expansion, reachability, and graph-grounded context collection\n- shortest paths for explanation chains, cost-based routing, and concept navigation\n- centrality for \"start here\" and graph importance surfaces\n- community detection for clustering and workspace organization\n- matching and flow for assignment and constrained planning\n- topological sort and cycle detection for dependency validation\n- subgraph isomorphism for pattern queries and reusable templates\n\nComplexity reporting under the evidence constraint:\n- the report cannot cite external textbooks or vendor docs\n- so complexity must be tracked as a template until Twilite-published docs exist\n\nWhat should still be decided now:\n- which edge types participate in DAG constraints\n- whether negative weights have any meaning at all\n- how much explanation determinism the AI layer needs\n- which algorithms must run incrementally vs in batch\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
