    {
      "id": "research-storage-integration",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Data Structures, Storage, and Integration",
      "position": {
        "x": -160,
        "y": 540
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 760,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Data Structures, Storage Options, and Integration Patterns\n\nIn-memory structures to evaluate:\n- adjacency list for sparse interactive queries\n- adjacency matrix only for specific dense or edge-existence-heavy workloads\n- edge list for interchange and append-only event logs\n\nPragmatic Twilite hybrid:\n- adjacency list for live runtime and canvas interactions\n- append-only edge/event list for persistence and replay\n- derived indexes for hot query surfaces\n\nPersistence backend options:\n- in-app persisted adjacency plus event log\n- property graph storage\n- external graph database\n- RDF / triple-store style semantics if ontology becomes central\n\nIntegration pattern to favor:\n- all edits normalize into a graph-change event stream\n- indexers maintain type/property/text/embedding lookup surfaces\n- query APIs are split by budget and caller class: UI, agent, analytics\n- expensive layout and clustering work should be treated as explicit compute jobs\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
