    {
      "id": "research-benchmarks",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Performance and Benchmarking",
      "position": {
        "x": 1200,
        "y": 760
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 620,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Performance Considerations, Benchmarks, and Suggested Experiments\n\nPerformance is product behavior in Twilite.\n\nBenchmark dimensions:\n- memory footprint and index overhead\n- p50 / p95 / p99 latency for interactive graph queries\n- throughput for update ingestion and index maintenance\n- metric and layout stability under small edits\n- cost of producing human-readable explanations for AI suggestions\n\nSuggested benchmark suite:\n- neighborhood expansion on the canvas\n- agent-safe top-k explanation paths\n- incremental update stress under bursts and merges\n- batch analytics cadence for clustering and ranking\n- event-log replay and state-hash verification\n\nStandard metrics to record early:\n- `|V|`, `|E|`, edge-type count, average and max degree\n- update mix percentages\n- query mix percentages\n- explicit UI vs batch latency budgets\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
