    {
      "id": "research-sources",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "twilite.zone Sources Used",
      "position": {
        "x": -820,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "### Sources Used\n\nAvailable public evidence from `twilite.zone` established:\n- Twilite as a persistent graph workspace where ideas connect and evolve\n- explicit graph framing: every node is a thought, every edge is a relationship\n- collaboration with an AI assistant that can understand the graph\n- the graph as durable, portable, and shared between humans and agents\n- public labels indicating deeper areas such as Core Ontology, Node Class Library, and Twilite Documentation\n\nImportant limit:\n- deeper technical docs were not retrievable in citable form under the strict site-only constraint\n- so this graph is an implementation decision framework, not a sourced benchmark sheet\n",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
